                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum from Mr. <persName type="from">Takahira</persName>
                        to Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Japanese Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Copy of telegram from Baron Komura to Mr. Takahira, received December 4,
                    1902:</p>
                <p>“His Excellency Buck, while attending duck-hunting party December 4, taken
                    suddenly ill and died.</p>
                <p>“Convey to the United States Government deepest condolence of Imperial
                    Government.”</p>
            </div>
